            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>sweet potato</strong> and <strong>lamb mince</strong> to the pan and cook for 5 min or until the lamb has browned and the sweet potato is starting to colour</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>,<strong> </strong>then add the <strong>stock</strong> to the pan, cover with a lid and cook for 10 min or until the sweet potato is fork-tender and the lamb mince is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
